GET:
    Used to retrieve data from the backend/websites/API.
    Example: 
        Fetching user details.
    Problems:
        Limited data in query string (max size limit).
        All data is visible in the URL (less secure).

POST:
    Used to send data to the server(backend) to "create" or "update" a resource.
    Example: 
        Creating a new user.
    Advantages:
        No size limit for data.
        Data is sent in the request body (more secure).
 